<paragraph blockId="2.[136,778,511,853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,440,581,607]" pageId="2" pageNumber="278">Amended diagnosis.</emphasis>
Larval stage with anterior part of head (and mouthparts?) drawn out into anteriorly projecting unpaired beak-like structure, leading to triangular head shape in dorsal view. Antennae short with few elements. A single pair of palps (unclear if maxillary or labial), with few elements. Prothorax large, broader than head, further posterior trunk segments similar in width, only very posterior ones narrower.
</paragraph>
